    "In what follows, we introduce these common challenges and discuss the associated research opportunities.C1-1 -Data Imbalance in Software Vulnerability Detection (In DevOps Development).",
    "Chakraborty et al. [25] observed that the performance of deep learning (DL)-based VD approaches could drop 73% of the F1-score due to the data imbalance issue.",
    "Thus, Yang et al. [260] further investigated the impact of data sampling on the effectiveness of existing state-of-the-art (SOTA) DL-based VD approaches.",
    "Their discovery revealed that, in DL-based VD, employing over-sampling proves more beneficial than under-sampling.",
    "Despite this observation, their experimental findings indicate a persistent challenge: a notable proportion of cases (ranging from 33% to 58%) where decisions were not determined by the presence of vulnerable statements."
